1) What is Spring Boot?
2) Spring-boot-Starter
3) Application.properties
4) @RestController
5) SpringBoot Actuator


1) What is Spring Boot?
      *   Spring Boot is an open-source Java framework used to 
          create a Micro Service. 
      *   Spring boot is developed by Pivotal Team, and it provides
          a faster way to set up and an easier, configure, 
          and run both simple and web-based applications. 
      *   It is a combination of Spring Framework and 
          Embedded Servers. 
      *   The main goal of Spring Boot is to reduce development, 
          unit test, and integration test time and in Spring Boot, 
          there is no requirement for XML configuration.

2) Spring-boot-Starter
      * spring-boot-starter is a core dependency in Spring Boot applications.
          It provides essential features like auto-configuration, logging 
          and YAML support.

          What it enables you to do Once added, you can:
              * Create REST controllers using @RestController
              * Handle HTTP requests with @GetMapping, @PostMapping, etc.
              * Automatically start a web server when you run your application
          EX :-
               <dependency>
                    <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
                    <artifactId>spring-boot-starter</artifactId>
               </dependency>


3) Application.properties
     The application.properties file is a central configuration file used to define
     various application settings, including database connectivity.
                                   or
     The application.properties file in a Spring boot project is a configuration
     file used to define various settings and behaviours of your application. It allows
     you to customize how your spring boot app runs without changing the code.

     Ex :-
        application.properties file              DempApp.java
        ------------------------------          --------------------------------
        |  #configure server port    |          | @RestController                   |
        | server.port=8080           |          | public class DemoApp{             |
        |                            |          |    @Value("${coach.name}")        |
        |  #configure my props       |          |     private String coach.name;    |
        |  coach.name=Balu           |          |     @Value("${team.name}")        |
        |  team.name=The BBS Crew    |          |     private String teamName;      |
        ------------------------------          --------------------------------

4) @RestController
          @RestController is a specialzed annotation introduced in Spring 4.0, that is 
          used to create RESTful web services.
     DEF:-  
          * It combines @Controller and @ResponseBody, which means that the methods in a class
            annotated with @RestController will return data directly as JSON or XML, rather
             than rendering a view.

          Ex:-
               |--------------------------------------------------
               | @RestController                                   |
               | public class Demo{                                |
               |                                                   |
               |    @GetMapping("/hello")                          |
               |    public String sayHelo(){                       |
               |          return "Hello, wworld!";                 |
               |     }                                             |
               | }                                                 |
               |---------------------------------------------------|


5) SpringBoot Actuator
          Spring Boot Actuator is a powerful feature in Spring Boot that provides production-ready tools 
          to help your monitor and manage your application. 
        * It exposes various REST endpoints that give insights into the application's health, metrics,
            environment and more ...
        * 	
                    -----------------------------------------------------------------------
                    |      <dependency>                                                   |
          		|	     <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>                 |
          		|	     <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-actuator</artifactId>       |
          		|      </dependency>                                                  |
                    -----------------------------------------------------------------------

          Key features :
               - Health checks (     /actuator/health     )   
                     Health info about your application. Check status of our app up or down.
                    output : - {"status" : "UP" }
               - Metrics (     /actuator/metrics     )
               - Beans  - List of all beans registered in the Spring application context
               - Mappings  - List of all @requestMappins paths
               - Environment info (     /actuator/env     )
               - Thread dumps, beans, loggers, etc.
               - Easily integrates with monitoring tools like Prometheus, Grafana and Spring Boot Admin.

            Exposing Endpoints :-
            -----------------------
               * By default, only /health is exposed
               * The /info endpoint can provide info about your application
               * to expose /info
                    >  application.properties
                    -----------------------------------------------------------------------
                    |      management.endpoints.web.exposure.include=health,info            |
                    |      management.info.env.enabled=true                                 |
                    -----------------------------------------------------------------------
               * To expose all actuator endpoints over HTTP use "*"
                    -----------------------------------------------------------------------
                    |         management.endpoints.web.exposure.include="                  |
                    -----------------------------------------------------------------------
             Info Endpoint :-
             ---------------
               */info gives info about your application.
               * Default is empty 
                    output :- { }
               * To cutomise info endpoints or update with our info
                    we have to update application.properties with our app info
                  ------------------------------------------------------------------------
                  |    info.app.name=My Super Cool APP                                   |
                  |     info.app.description=A Crazy and fun App, yahoooooo!             |
                  |     info.app.version= 1.0.0                                          |
                  ------------------------------------------------------------------------

                    >  now when we search -  http://localhost:8080/actuator/health the output will be
                         ---------------------------------------------------------------------
                         |     {                                                             |
                         |       "app": {                                                    |
                         |         "name": "My Super Cool App",                              |
                         |         "description": "A crazy fun app, yoohooo!",               |
                         |         "version": "1.0.0"                                        |
                         |       }                                                           |
                         |     }                                                             |
                         --------------------------------------------------------------------|






